<!DOCTYPE rkplugin>
<document>
    <code file="one_sample_t_test.js"/>
    <help file="one_sample_t_test.rkh"/>
    
    <logic>
        <connect client="filter_embed.variable" governor="variable.available" />
        <convert id="grouped_mode" mode="equals" sources="grouped.state" standard="1" />
        <connect client="groups.visible" governor="grouped_mode" />
    </logic>
    
    <dialog label="t-test for the mean of one population">
        <tabbook>
            <tab id="tab_variables" label="Variable">
                <row id="row_vars">
                    <varselector id="selector" label="Select variable" />
                    <column>
                        <varslot id="variable" label="Mean of" source="selector" types="number" required="true" />
                        <checkbox id="grouped" label="Means by groups" value_unchecked="0" checked="false" />
                        <varslot id="groups" label="Grouping variable(s):" types="factor" source="selector" multi="true" required="true" />
                        <embed id="filter_embed" component="rkTeaching::filter_embed"/>
                        <stretch />
                    </column>
                </row>
            </tab>
            <tab id="tab_settings" label="Test options">
                <row>
                    <column id="hypotesis_col">
                        <input id="mean" label="Mean value in null hypothesis" size="small" initial="0" />
                        <radio id="hypothesis" label="Alternative hypothesis">
                            <option value="two.sided" label="Two-sided (&#8800;)" />
                            <option value="greater" label="Greater (&gt;)" />
                            <option value="less" label="Less (&lt;)" />
                        </radio>
                        <frame id="confint_frame" label="Confidence interval for the mean" checkable="true" checked="true" value="1">
                            <spinbox id="conflevel" label="Confidence level" type="real" min="0" max="0.99" initial="0.95" />
                        </frame>
                    </column>
                </row>
                <stretch />
            </tab>
        </tabbook>
    </dialog>
    
    <wizard label="t-test for the mean of one population wizard">
        <page>
            <text>
                Insert the numeric variable to test.
            </text>
            <copy id="row_vars"/>
            <stretch/>
        </page>
        <page>
            <text>
                <p>Enter the value of the mean in the null hypothesis</p>
            </text>
            <copy id="mean"/>
            <stretch/>
        </page>
        <page>
            <text>
                <p>Select the type of alternative hypothesis to test:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Check two-sided you have no assumption about what mean is greater.</li>
                    <li>Check greater if you assume that the mean of the first population is greater than the mean of the second population.</li>
                    <li>Check less if you assume that the mean of the first population is less than the mean of the second population.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>The one-sided hypothesis tends to increase the power of the test.</p>
            </text>
            <copy id="hypothesis"/>
            <stretch/>
        </page>
        <page>
            <text>
                <p>If you wants a confidence interval to estimate the mean of the populations check the box and enter the desired confidence level (a 95% of confidence correspond to a 5% of significance).</p>
            </text>
            <copy id="confint_frame"/>
            <stretch/>
        </page>
    </wizard>
</document>
